If you need certificates or information on your items after last nights auction please contact Dillon Denisen at 507-269-5572 or ask any board member.

The GMEF board would like thank Meyerhofer’s for use of their building, the fireman for the meal and drinks, to everyone that donated items, purchased items, area farmers for corn donations and the many volunteers that made last nights auction a success!! We are blessed to live in such a great community!!

This is a Female American Brittany (Brittany Spaniel) She comes out of some of the best bloodlines in the nation. She has a micro chip for identification and is current on all her shots. She should grow to about 32 pounds and 18" tall when full grown. She will be on the live auction Saturday!!
Thanks Ben Jacobsen and crew for this great donation !!

post_text:
Lot 29

The Grand Meadow Education Foundation is hosting a hoodie auction on our Facebook page just in time for the cold weather! Several local businesses donated hoodies for the auction. How it will work:

We will post a picture of each hoodie including size. If you like the hoodie, simply place a bid by commenting on the picture and include your bid amount. If you are the highest bid, once bidding stalls for 24 hours you will win the hoodie!

Checks can be made out to Grand Meadow Education Foundation and can be picked up at Dillon Denisen’s office in the Grand Meadow Business Center.

ALL proceeds go directly to the Grand Meadow Education Foundation.

Thank you for your support.

PS: tag and share with your friends

The Grand Meadow Education Foundation is hosting a hoodie auction on our Facebook page just in time for the cold weather! Several local businesses donated hoodies for the auction. How it will work:

We will post a picture of each hoodie including size. If you like the hoodie, simply place a bid by commenting on the picture and include your bid amount. If you are the highest bid, once bidding stalls for 24 hours you will win the hoodie!

Checks can be made out to Grand Meadow Education Foundation and can be picked up at Dillon Denisen’s office in the Grand Meadow Business Center.

ALL proceeds go directly to the Grand Meadow Education Foundation.

Thank you for your support.

PS: tag and share with your friends

post_text:
The winning bidder of this item is awarded two personalized hours of court time with J.P. Macura in the Spring of 2019. The location of this event will be Lakeville North High School
Players will be able to perform drills, ask questions, and learn some of the tenacious mindset it takes to excel at the highest level of basketball in the state of Minnesota, the NCAA, and now as J.P. works to continue his career professionally.

Some of the highlights up to this point from J.P. Macura’s career include:
• Leading Lakeville High School to a state Championship where he averaged 32.2 points and 6.5 rebounds his senior season
• Earning the Big East Conference Sixth Man Award by the Big East Coaches
• As a senior at Xavier helped his team earn a first ever No. 1 seed in the NCAA Tournament
• Finished his high school career with 1,811 points and college career with 1,491 points

We would like to thank J.P. for his support of the Grand Meadow Education Foundation as they continue to provide opportunities and promote education for the students of Grand Meadow.

post_text:
GREAT DONATION HERE!!

It is a pure bred AKC Registered white labs. A white lab is actually a yellow lab with a double recessive yellow gene. Akc still recognizes them as yellow on paperwork. But they are ivory white in color. They already have there dew claws removed and will have all of there shots done at 6 weeks. They are de-wormed as well. Remi's mom and dad were both field champions for waterfowl. And her dad had a dock jumping record for quite a few years but it was beat a few years ago.

Thanks Olson Tree Services for the donation!

post_text: The GMEF was proud to sponsor the 2nd quarter academic breakfast this past Friday, February 2nd. This breakfast is held to honor students in grades 7-12 that were on the A and B Honor rolls. 137 students qualified for this honor. Trevor Green was the student speaker. Representatives from the school board in attendance were Wanda Edge and Shavonn Eastlee. Paul Besel and Jacob Schwarz also spoke during this event.
text: The GMEF was proud to sponsor the 2nd quarter academic breakfast this past Friday, February 2nd. This breakfast is held to honor students in grades 7-12 that were on the A and B Honor rolls. 137 students qualified for this honor. Trevor Green was the student speaker. Representatives from the school board in attendance were Wanda Edge and Shavonn Eastlee. Paul Besel and Jacob Schwarz also spoke during this event.

post_text: The GMEF presented dictionaries to the 3rd grade classes (35 students) this past Friday. Third grade teachers, Mrs. Arndorfer and Mrs. Rude were very pleased that the GMEF continues to supply each third grade student with their very own dictionary to be used during the school year.

post_text: In conjunction with the Grand Meadow Community Ed and Grand Meadow School we are proud to Announce that the same night as our Annual Auction we will also be holding a Fall Fun Fest. This will be for kids ages 4 and up and for parents to attend our event that evening at Crazy Jane’s. Kids will have games, music, pizza, crafts, popcorn, bounce house, and more. Parents will have a date night in town with live music, and dinner. Half the meals proceeds will go to the GMEF. Our Silent & Live Auctions will also be going on. By attending this event your showing your support for the Grand Meadow Schools and there students and staff. We hope to see you there!
